        <h3 class="style7">Inspection</h3>
        <ul class="style8"><li>All robots will be measured, inspected, and weighed to verify qualification.</li>
            <li>A digital scale will be used for determining mass.  </li>
            <li>The robot will be inspected to be sure it is non-damaging and generally safe.</li>
            <li>Records will be kept to facilitate dispute resolution and tie breaking. </li>
            <li>If any unmentioned query occurs, then the decision will be taken by the referee on the spot.</li>            
        </ul>
        </li>
        
        <li><h3 class="style7">Contestant Stoppage </h3>
            <ul><li class="style8">If the robot is malfunctioning or in a position in which damage could occur, it might be in the contestant's interest to halt the round and take the short-term loss.</li>
                <li class="style8">Communicating with the robot, attempting to distract (such as with an IR or laser emitter), or in any way attempting to interfere with the outcome is also considered signalling stoppage.</li>
            </ul>
        </li>

        <li><h3 class="style7">Referee Stoppage</h3>
        <p class="style8">At the referee's discretion, the referee may choose to restart a round if:<br /></p>
            <ul><li class="style8">No progress has been made in some period of time.</li>
            <li><span class="style8">The robots are hopelessly entangled or otherwise deadlocked.</li>
            <li>Both robots fail to start or both contestants signal stoppage.</span></li>
            </ul>
        </li>
    </ol>
